# {{AU}} In the days when [[Australia]] was a penal colony: a [[convict]] who had reached the end of his or her [[sentence]].  Also sometimes called an [[emancipist]], though that usually meant a convict who was [[pardon]]ed.  (Reference: [[w:Ernest Scott|Ernest Scott]], ''A Short History of Australia'', chapter V [http://gutenberg.net.au/pgaus.html#scott].)

